Literature Survey

Heart disease continues to be one of the most significant public health
 challenges worldwide. Many healthcare organizations use Business 
 Intelligence tools to analyze medical datasets and improve patient 
 care.

Research shows that data visualization tools such as 
Tableau help transform raw healthcare data into meaningful insights 
through dashboards and interactive reports. SQL databases provide
 efficient storage and querying capabilities, while Flask enables 
 deployment of dashboards through web applications.

Several studies emphasize that factors such as age, cholesterol, 
blood pressure, chest pain type, and lifestyle habits are strongly 
associated with heart disease. Visual analytics improves understanding 
of these relationships and supports preventive healthcare strategies.